BARLOW-MOORE TOBACCO COMPANY v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 7589. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 28, 1937. Woodward, Dawson & Hobson, of Louisville, Ky., for appellant. Bunk Gardner, of Louisville, Ky., for appellee.

Before HICKS and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

*1001HICKS, Circuit Judge.

On motion of appellant, it is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed, without prejudice at the cost of appellant.
